<title type="html"><![CDATA[5/23 (Thur.) Losing Our Coral Reefs/ Is the world running out of fresh water? (Host: Alison)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=283&amp;p=299#p299"><![CDATA[
Session One: Losing Our Coral Reefs<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://blogs.ei.columbia.edu/2011/06/13/losing-our-coral-reefs/">https://blogs.ei.columbia.edu/2011/06/1 ... ral-reefs/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion:<br />1. Have you heard of the global issue of coral bleaching before and how do you feel about it?<br />2. What are the benefits of having healthy coral reefs?<br />3. What causes the coral reefs bleaching and what are the impacts of losing them?<br />4. What sort of things we can do to help and protect coral reefs?<br />5. Have you seen any films or TV programmes on coral reefs that you would like to share?<br /><br /><br />Session Two: Is the world running out of fresh water?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20170412-is-the-world-running-out-of-fresh-water">http://www.bbc.com/future/story/2017041 ... resh-water</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Discussion:<br />1. Have you ever experienced water shortage before? When was it and what was it like?<br />2. What sort of things consume a lot of water?<br />3. What would happen if there was a severe water shortage around the globe, and how can we prevent it?<br />4. Can you think of any ways to save water and what are the benefits of doing so?<br /><br />Suggested Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. free talk <br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. first topic discussion <br />8:10 p.m. --8:20 p.m. Presentation <br />8:20 p.m.-- 8:40 p.m. Sharing time : articles &amp; other experiences. <br />8:40 p.m.-- 9.:15 p.m. second topic discussion <br />9:15 p.m.-- 9:30 p.m. Presentation<br />speaker time : 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time : 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=13721">morris</a> — Fri May 17, 2019 1:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
